1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,667
I changed a rollout from ten percent to twenty.

2
00:00:03,667 --> 00:00:05,500
The scary part?

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,500
An agent can confidently bring back the old answer.

4
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:11,200
In production, stale truth is worse than no memory.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,667
So I built DREAM.

6
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:24,733
Qwen understands what experience means; deterministic lifecycle rules decide what can come back.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,500
This is the public build.

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,733
It is running in Singapore, on Alibaba Function Compute.

9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
First, I set the canary at ten percent, for thirty minutes.

10
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,167
Qwen recognizes the preference.

11
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:43,567
It gives me an inspectable receipt.

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,167
Then I change it to twenty percent for forty-five minutes.

13
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:55,333
Qwen catches the conflict; DREAM keeps only the new value active.

14
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,833
In a fresh session, DREAM returns twenty percent in nineteen of sixty-four tokens.

15
00:01:04,833 --> 00:01:07,767
The old instruction never enters context.

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
The test I cared about was persistence.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:22,667
I saved a Qwen-curated memory, rebuilt the same source, and forced a new Function Compute instance.

18
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:28,167
The instance ID changed; the memory, decision, and Qwen receipt did not.

19
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:33,933
Twenty simultaneous conflicting writes also succeeded, leaving one active truth and nineteen historical versions.

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:48,667
In a clearly labeled synthetic evaluation, the same Qwen model improved from 25.3 to 48.7 across seven paired cases.

21
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:57,600
A separate twenty-four-case lifecycle suite passed every recall, stale-leak, and token-budget check.

22
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,833
Underneath: Angular and FastAPI on Function Compute; Qwen Cloud for meaning;

23
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:10,333
Tablestore transactions for one current truth; and temporary credentials from a narrow RAM role.

24
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,000
I do not want longer history.

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,433
I want one current, reviewable truth, for the next decision.
